100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On December 5, 1925, the world was abuzz with news of the ongoing Locarno Treaties, as European nations sought to solidify peace after the Great War. In the United States, the Supreme Court ruled on the controversial case of Meyer v. Nebraska, impacting educational freedoms. Additionally, the discovery of a significant oil field in Texas hinted at a booming economy ahead. Meanwhile, political tensions continued to rise in various parts of the globe, particularly in the Middle East and Eastern Europe.
